From 6c695c89abede9f25c1ddba18c9ecd5cfcdf5f66 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 23 Jul 2026 10:07:42 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 5/6] Add accent color wheel, font picker, and PT-PT/EN
 language toggle with full app translation

- Settings: replace the 6 fixed accent swatches with a drag/click hue
  wheel (ColorWheel component), storing a free-form accentHue that
  overrides the legacy named accentColor when set.
- Settings: add a font pairing picker (Modern/Grotesk/System/Serif/Mono)
  applied app-wide via --font-body/--font-display CSS custom properties.
- New i18n layer (LanguageContext + translations.js) with PT-PT and EN
  dictionaries; PT-PT is the default. Every page and shared component
  now renders through t() instead of hardcoded English strings.
  Login/Register render static PT-PT copy since no session exists yet
  to carry a language preference; the toggle lives in Settings.
- Settings/schema: add accentHue, fontFamily and language columns.
